Summary: Serial backend on Windows hangs on simultaneous input/output
Class: bug
Present-in: 0.60
Fixed-in: r8410 2009-01-13
Content-type: text/x-html-body

<p>
PuTTY 0.60 for Windows can lock up when using the serial backend and
there is simultaneous input and output.

<p>
For instance, doing <tt>more&nbsp;/var/adm/messages</tt> to a Unix
system and pressing and holding 'j' to scroll is reported to be
sufficient to cause the session to lock up.
